args: Thank you one and all for attending\nour show today!
It's almost time for the curtain to rise,\nso please take your seats!
Hey, Fritz. Full house again today, huh?
Sure is—and I owe it all to your backing.
All right, time to get this show on the—
Blast! Haven't even started yet,\nand we've already got a heckler.
Let's go see what's going on.
I'm going HOME!\nI don't wanna see a circus!
At least give it a try, darling.
I'm so sorry for how he's behaving.
It's all right—but is something actually\nthe matter, or is he simply having\na difficult childhood moment?
The show has yet to begin, after all,\nso there's no way he can judge its\npossible entertainment value yet.
Of COURSE it's gonna be boring!
Don't be so rude! Oh, I do apologize\nfor my little snookums.
I brought him hoping to cheer him up,\nbut perhaps that was a bad idea.
Yes. You see, my husband—his father—\npassed away somewhat recently.
I don't think I've seen him smile once\nsince that terrible day.
And you were hoping the circus\nmight change that.
That's right. But all we're doing is causing\ntrouble for all the other customers,\nso we should probably leave.
Our shows are the finest in the land;\nI swear we will make your son smile.
Screw the circus! I'm not watching!
No need to be like that.\nThe circus is a delight!
No it isn't! It might make other people\ngrin like a bunch of idiots, but not me!
I don't wanna do what idiots do!
What did you just say, you little brat?
F-Fritz! Don't talk to him like that!
So you think our guests are idiots, do you?
Y-yeah! Anyone who likes something\nthis dumb HAS to be an idiot!
In that case...I challenge you. Consider it\na little wager between men.
I wager that when our show is over,\nyou'll say it was fun.
If you find it fun, I win.\nIf you find it boring, you win.
What do you say? Of course,\nif you're scared that you'll lose,\nyou don't have to—
I-I'm just as much a man as you,\nmister! You're on!
In that case, follow me to the VIP seats.
Oh dear... What should I do?
Go with him. Don't worry—he'll make\nyour son happy again.
Thank you all for attending our show today.\nWe look forward to having you again!
I had so much fun! You're AMAZING!
I can't believe you could hit all those\ntargets from so far away! Soooo cool!
I told you the circus was fun!
I wanna be like you when I grow up!
I wanna make people happy just like you!
W-well, that's a fine goal overall,\nbut I wouldn't try to become like me.
I think he's a fine role model.
I mean, when it comes to dagger-throwing,\nFritz is a pro among pros who never lets\nhis target escape.
And today he did the same for your spirit,\nwhich is probably why you want to be\nlike him, right?
I would be happy if he grew into a man\nas lovely as you, sir.
Thank you so much for reminding him\nthat it's okay to smile again.
I'm gonna come see you again sometime.\nBye for today!
Why did you tell that kid\nI was a good role model?
I don't think a former thief who still lives\na selfish life is someone for a kid to\ntry and emulate.
Better to try and be a decent,\nrespectable guy like you.
I don't think that's true at all—especially\nafter seeing you today.
Do you remember when you first told me\nwhy you joined the troupe?
You said you wanted to bring joy to others.
Well, I think today was the perfect\nexample of that.
That boy had just lost his father,\nand yet you were able to help him\nforget that pain for a short while.
I know you regret what you did in the past,\nbut now you're making amends for it.
There's a lot to respect in the way you live.
I think you've found the life you want.
You never miss anything you set\nyour eyes on, after all.
Heh. You really know how to one-up a guy.
I was just thinking I'd never be able to\nlive an honest life like you do...
But now I realize I'm already on that path,\nwhich means I can't back down.
Maybe it's time for me to take pride\nin the life I've carved out for myself.
I can't be having that kid regretting he\nchose me as his role model, after all.
I know you can do it, Fritz.
